{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c53693d7-9e9f-4d50-b67b-1fe4056ec37d","content":"Use `dotnet watch test` with the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\"\n```\n\nThis will:\n- **`dotnet watch test`** — re-run tests automatically when you save a file\n- **`--filter \"FullyQualifiedName~...\"`** — run only tests whose name contains that string\n\nThe `~` operator means \"contains\", so you don't need the full namespace. You can also filter by just the method name:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"Name=ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\"\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"36cd6ed5-52cc-4b11-a46f-0ee1f9adc371","outputTokens":163,"requestId":"084B:2C68A2:1676E01:17DE192:6A04604F"},"id":"7f39e5e2-e86e-4af1-a829-ff947b1ca816","timestamp":"2026-05-13T11:28:22.342Z","parentId":"1dbbe53d-a492-403b-a66a-7e253c905b5a"}
